\r\n of it.\nTherefore, true fearlessness can be attained only in the non-dual s=\r\ntate of\nSelf, where no other thing exists.\n\nTo illustrate how fearlessness =\r\ncan be attained only when one attains the\nstate of Self, Sri Bhagavan used =\r\nto narrate the following story:\n\nAfter Lord Vishnu had killed Hiranya, Hira=\r\nnya=E2=80=99s son Prahlada was happily\nruling the kingdom.\n\nBut after some =\r\ntime, a fear arose in Prahlada. =E2=80=9CBecause Lord Vishnu is kind\nto me,=\r\n I am living safely. But if one day He becomes angry with me, He will\nkill =\r\nme just as He killed my father,=E2=80=9D thought Prahlada.\n\nBeing a great d=\r\nevotee of Lord Vishnu, Prahlada had no one else to turn to,\nso he\nprayed to=\r\n Him. The Lord immediately appeared before Prahlada,who then\nexplained his =\r\nfear and prayed for the state of fearlessness.\n\n=E2=80=9CYes,=E2=80=9D said=\r\n Lord Vishnu, =E2=80=9CYou are correct. By seeing me like this in name\nand =\r\nform, you cannot be free from fear.\n\nYou must see me within yourself. Only =\r\nwhen you thus realize me to be not\ndifferent from yourself, will you attain=\r\n the state of fearlessness=E2=80=9D. Then\nthe Lord taught him the path of S=\r\nelf-enquiry. When Prahlada followed the\nLord=E2=80=99s instructions and rea=\r\nlized Self, he attained the state of\nfearlessness.\n\nThis story thus illustr=\r\nates that even God cannot serve as permanent refuge\nfrom fear so long as on=\r\ne retains the sense of difference [bheda-buddhi].\nOnly by attaining the non=\r\n-dual Self can one become truly and permanently\nfree from fear.\n\nSource: GU=\r\nRU VACHAKA KOVAI The Light of Supreme Truth or THE COLLECTION OF\nGURU=E2=80=\r\n=99S SAYINGS translated from original Tamil By Sadhu Om and Michael James\n\n=\r\nGuru Vachaka Kovai is the biggest collection of Bhagavan=E2=80=99s spoken t=\r\neachings\nthat was thoroughly checked and revised by him during his lifetime=\r\n. As such\nit has a unique place in the